    "System.Description": "<div><br> </div><div>Build a comprehensive user management interface for school administrators to create, view, and manage users in the Rostering system. </div><div>This Includes user creation, user list with search filtering and sorting, user details view. </div><div><br> </div>",
    "Microsoft.VSTS.Common.AcceptanceCriteria": "<h3>AC1: Display User List </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> I am logged in as School Admin<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I navigate to /users<br><strong>THEN</strong> I see paginated list of users in my school<br><br><h3>AC2: Search Users </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> I am on user list<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I type in search box<br><strong>THEN</strong> list filters with debounced search<br><strong>AND</strong> shows loading indicator<br><br><h3>AC3: Filter by Role </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> I am on user list<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I select Teacher from role filter<br><strong>THEN</strong> list shows only Teachers<br><strong>AND</strong> filters can be combined<br><br><h3>AC4: Create User with Valid Data </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> I click New User<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I fill form with valid data and submit<br><strong>THEN</strong> API called, success message shown<br><strong>AND</strong> password reset link displayed<br><strong>AND</strong> list refreshes<br><br><h3>AC5: Validate Email Uniqueness </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> creating new user<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I enter existing email<br><strong>THEN</strong> error shown on blur<br><strong>AND</strong> Create button disabled<br><br><h3>AC6: Validate Required Fields </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> creating new user<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I leave required field empty<br><strong>THEN</strong> error message displays<br><strong>AND</strong> Create button disabled<br><br><h3>AC7: Resend Password Reset </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> viewing user details<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I click Resend Password Reset<br><strong>THEN</strong> confirmation modal appears<br><br><h3>AC8: Deactivate User </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> viewing active user<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I click Deactivate<br><strong>THEN</strong> confirmation modal with warning<br><br><h3>AC9: Reactivate User </h3><strong>GIVEN</strong> viewing inactive user<br><strong>WHEN</strong> I click Reactivate<br><strong>THEN</strong> confirmation modal appears<br><strong>AND</strong> status changes to Active<br><br><h3><br> </h3><br>",
